From: Jason Germino <jasongermino@gmail.com>
Date: Sun, 22 Jun 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] input: xpad: skip Xbox 360 vendor init message by default

The "magic message" is a vendor control request (bRequest=0x01,
bmRequestType=0xC1, wValue=0x0100) sent to EP0 when userspace first
opens the input device.  The comment already notes it is only needed by
"some" third-party Xbox 360 controllers.

8BitDo SN30 Pro+ in X-input mode stalls this request (returns EREMOTEIO)
and then repeatedly resets its USB connection on Allwinner A733 with the
BSP EHCI TT controller.  The controller worked on kernel 5.15 BSP but
regressed on 6.6 BSP, indicating the EP0 STALL/TT recovery path changed.

Add skip_magic_message (default: true) so the control transfer is not
sent.  Controllers that need it can disable the skip with:
  xpad.skip_magic_message=0

Signed-off-by: Jason Germino <jasongermino@gmail.com>
---
 drivers/input/joystick/xpad.c | 14 ++++++++++++--
 1 file changed, 12 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/input/joystick/xpad.c b/drivers/input/joystick/xpad.c
--- a/drivers/input/joystick/xpad.c
+++ b/drivers/input/joystick/xpad.c
@@ -117,6 +117,12 @@
 module_param(sticks_to_null, bool, S_IRUGO);
 MODULE_PARM_DESC(sticks_to_null, "Do not map sticks at all for unknown pads");

+static bool skip_magic_message = true;
+module_param(skip_magic_message, bool, S_IRUGO | S_IWUSR);
+MODULE_PARM_DESC(skip_magic_message,
+	"Skip Xbox 360 vendor init control message (default on); some third-party "
+	"controllers stall it and then reset their USB connection");
+
 static bool auto_poweroff = true;
 module_param(auto_poweroff, bool, S_IWUSR | S_IRUGO);
 MODULE_PARM_DESC(auto_poweroff, "Power off wireless controllers on suspend");
@@ -1794,10 +1800,12 @@
 			return error;
 		}
 	}
-	if (xpad->xtype == XTYPE_XBOX360) {
+	if (xpad->xtype == XTYPE_XBOX360 && !skip_magic_message) {
 		/*
 		 * Some third-party controllers Xbox 360-style controllers
-		 * require this message to finish initialization.
+		 * require this message to finish initialization.  Others (e.g.
+		 * 8BitDo in X-input mode) stall it and then reset their USB
+		 * connection.  Skipped by default via skip_magic_message.
 		 */
 		u8 dummy[20];

